# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: StoryBeginnings | Scene: ChooseThePath
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Following the coronation, Sarah had gone straight back to her bedroom and fallen asleep."
    new "Following the coronation, Sarah had gone straight back to her bedroom and fallen asleep."

    old "It was deep in the night, and after the festivities had ended, the castle was silent as the grave."
    new "It was deep in the night, and after the festivities had ended, the castle was silent as the grave."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah found herself rising from her sleep."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah found herself rising from her sleep."

    old "Half awake, she heard the sounds of someone moving around her bedroom."
    new "Half awake, she heard the sounds of someone moving around her bedroom."

    old "Sarah pushed herself up and whispered into the darkness."
    new "Sarah pushed herself up and whispered into the darkness."

    old "Who is in here?"
    new "Who is in here?"

    old "A familiar voice responded."
    new "A familiar voice responded."

    old "Sarah, it's me."
    new "Sarah, it's me."

    old "Sarah sighed, relieved to hear Kate's voice."
    new "Sarah sighed, relieved to hear Kate's voice."

    old "Sarah felt her heart rate rise."
    new "Sarah felt her heart rate rise."

    old "Kate usually came into her bedroom at night for a single purpose."
    new "Kate usually came into her bedroom at night for a single purpose."

    old "Kate, I'm really tired, I don't know if tonight I can..."
    new "Kate, I'm really tired, I don't know if tonight I can..."

    old "Kate interrupted her."
    new "Kate interrupted her."

    old "That's not why I'm here Sarah."
    new "That's not why I'm here Sarah."

    old "There was something very serious about Kate. Sarah was confused."
    new "There was something very serious about Kate. Sarah was confused."

    old "What are you doing here?"
    new "What are you doing here?"

    old "I'm so glad it's you, what are you doing here?"
    new "I'm so glad it's you, what are you doing here?"

    old "Kate sat down on the edge of the bed."
    new "Kate sat down on the edge of the bed."

    old "Sarah...I need to tell you something, and I know it will be a lot to process, but I need you to listen. Can you promise me that you will?"
    new "Sarah...I need to tell you something, and I know it will be a lot to process, but I need you to listen. Can you promise me that you will?"

    old "Sarah was now fully awake, sitting upright in her bed."
    new "Sarah was now fully awake, sitting upright in her bed."

    old "Kate...you can tell me anything. What is it?"
    new "Kate...you can tell me anything. What is it?"

    old "Kate looked to the ceiling, as if the words she was looking for were written up there."
    new "Kate looked to the ceiling, as if the words she was looking for were written up there."

    old "I've not been honest with you...not entirely."
    new "I've not been honest with you...not entirely."

    old "I didn't just come here because your father had passed."
    new "I didn't just come here because your father had passed."

    old "Sarah could feel her heart beat in her throat. Whatever it was that Kate tried to tell her, it was something big."
    new "Sarah could feel her heart beat in her throat. Whatever it was that Kate tried to tell her, it was something big."

    old "Several months ago, I was contacted...by your father."
    new "Several months ago, I was contacted...by your father."

    old "Sarah sat listening, stunned."
    new "Sarah sat listening, stunned."

    old "He reached out to me in Lethram, across the sea, where I was stationed. He told me that there were dangerous forces out there, seeking to harm you."
    new "He reached out to me in Lethram, across the sea, where I was stationed. He told me that there were dangerous forces out there, seeking to harm you."

    old "He said that he couldn't tell me much more than that, but he asked me, as your old friend, to come back to the castle, should anything happen to him..."
    new "He said that he couldn't tell me much more than that, but he asked me, as your old friend, to come back to the castle, should anything happen to him..."

    old "Kate paused."
    new "Kate paused."

    old "And he asked me to take you to safety...across the sea, to Lethram."
    new "And he asked me to take you to safety...across the sea, to Lethram."

    old "Sarah found it hard to process what she was hearing. Her friend had kept this secret from her, but so had her father. Did her father know that he had been in danger all this time?"
    new "Sarah found it hard to process what she was hearing. Her friend had kept this secret from her, but so had her father. Did her father know that he had been in danger all this time?"

    old "He paid the mercenary company I work for a small fortune, if we vowed to keep you safe in Lethram."
    new "He paid the mercenary company I work for a small fortune, if we vowed to keep you safe in Lethram."

    old "When we heard of your father's death, we knew that we had to come and save you. That's why I'm here, to honor what I promised your father."
    new "When we heard of your father's death, we knew that we had to come and save you. That's why I'm here, to honor what I promised your father."

    old "Another pause."
    new "Another pause."

    old "Sarah, you need to come with me, to Lethram. It's the only place where we can keep you safe. But, we need to leave tonight, right now. There is a ship waiting for us in the harbor."
    new "Sarah, you need to come with me, to Lethram. It's the only place where we can keep you safe. But, we need to leave tonight, right now. There is a ship waiting for us in the harbor."

    old "Sarah's mind was spinning. The mystery of her father's death only grew, now Kate revealed herself to be her father's secret agent...and now she had to leave in the dead of night."
    new "Sarah's mind was spinning. The mystery of her father's death only grew, now Kate revealed herself to be her father's secret agent...and now she had to leave in the dead of night."

    old "Sarah's eyes had become used to the dark, and she could see her friend's eyes, glittering with tears."
    new "Sarah's eyes had become used to the dark, and she could see her friend's eyes, glittering with tears."

    old "Sarah, please, come with me."
    new "Sarah, please, come with me."

    old "Kate reaches out her hand."
    new "Kate reaches out her hand."

    old "Reach out and grab Kate's hand."
    new "Reach out and grab Kate's hand."

    old "No, I can't leave Thomas. This is crazy."
    new "No, I can't leave Thomas. This is crazy."

